TY  - JOUR
AU  - Williams, Joseph T.
T1  - Equilibrium and Options on Real Assets
PY  - 1993
Y1  - 1993/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/6.4.825
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 6
IS  - 4
SP  - 825
EP  - 850
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - In aggregate, options on real and financial assets can have very different properties. Typically, the good or service produced by a real asset has a finite elasticity of demand, and developers have finite capacities. Also, the supply of options can be limited, and developers can be less than perfectly competitive. In a subgame, perfect Nash equilibrium with these properties, the optimal exercise policy, and resulting values of developed and undeveloped assets are calculated explicitly. The novel comparative statics are discussed in detail.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/6.4.825
ER  - 



